summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Western Sahara, 
Reaffirming commitment to assist parties to achieve a just, lasting and mutually acceptable political solution providing self-determination for Western Sahara's people,
 Reiterating call for cooperation to end impasse and achieve progress towards solution,
Having considered Secretary-General's report,
Decides to extend MINURSO's mandate until 30 April 2005; 
Requests Secretary-General's report on situation before mandate end and interim report within 3 months on evolution, mission size and concept; 
Calls on Member States to consider voluntary contributions for Confidence Building Measures; 
Decides to remain seized of matter
